# Project context (shared with Claude Code)

This repo uses `context/` as persistent memory across Cursor and Claude Code CLI. Do not maintain a separate Cursor-only history.

## On every task start

1. Read `context/history.md`, `context/decisions.md`, `context/gotchas.md`, `context/todo.md`
2. Read `CONVENTIONS.md` before writing code
3. If `context/` is missing, create the four files using the templates in `claude_config/agents/context-manager.md` (BOOTSTRAP section)

## On every task completion

1. Append a brief entry to `context/history.md` (date, task, what changed, files touched)
2. Append to `context/decisions.md` or `context/gotchas.md` when applicable
3. Update `context/todo.md` (done / in-progress / blocked)
4. Archive `context/history.md` entries older than 30 days to `context/archive/history-YYYY-MM.md`

Do not use `MEMORY.md` or `STATUS.md` (deprecated). Live tasks: `context/todo.md`. Session log: `context/history.md`.

## Full conventions

Also follow `CLAUDE.md` in the project root (agent routing, Definition of Done, git workflow). At session start in Cursor, invoke **session-start**. At session end, invoke **update-project-context**. Claude Code agents live in `.claude/agents/`; Cursor does not load those files automatically, but the same workflow applies.
